{
  "stem": "17526.5",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "Looking at the [INAUDIBLE], the tombstones, and reading the names on them was an experience I will never forget for the rest of my life.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "Bendin came alive again.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "All those familiar names, all those memories.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "Shortly before leaving the cemetery, I stumbled upon the stone of my grandmother.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "I never expected to find it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "It was then when it really hit home.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "I cried uncontrollably.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "I just couldn't get over it, that this beautiful stone withstood six decades of the most tragic events that befell our people.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "I called my brother and we both stood there in disbelief.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "I felt like my mother, my aunts, and all the descendants of this great bubbe of ours were looking over my shoulder and watching us.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "I almost could hear my mother whispering in my ear, [?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "Joseph, ?] I'm glad you came.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "Then we climbed out of there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "The underbrush and the overgrown branches were so thick that we actually climbed in and out of graves, or what once used to be graves.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "On the way out, the caretaker of the cemetery asked us if we found what we were looking for, and he told us that they-- that means [INAUDIBLE]-- the man that has restored it-- is trying to catalogue all the names so it will be easier to find who everyone is looking for.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "We left the cemetery and took another walk to town.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "At a site where once the great synagogue was situated right in front of the castle, we closed our eyes, again trying to figure out where and what it did-- where it-- what it did look like in our memories.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "What we saw is the castle neglected like a [INAUDIBLE] on a hillside.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
